@startuml

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<external>> LightBlue
    BackgroundColor<<storage>> LightYellow
    BackgroundColor<<processing>> LightGreen
    BackgroundColor<<frontend>> LightCoral
    BackgroundColor<<proxy>> LightGray
}

title Zilgraph Component Diagram - Deployment and Data Flow

package "External Services" {
    component [Zilliqa Blockchain] <<external>>
    component [Local Zil Seed Node API] <<external>>
}

package "Data Acquisition Layer" {
    component [Zilcrawler] <<processing>> as Crawler
    component [Crawler Manager] <<processing>> as CrawlerMgr
    component [Zilswap Interaction] <<processing>> as ZilswapInt
}

package "Data Storage Layer" {
    database "Elasticsearch" <<storage>> as ES
    database "MongoDB" <<storage>> as Mongo
}

package "Data Processing Layer" {
    component [Data Collector] <<processing>> as DataCollector
    component [Aggregator Classes] <<processing>> as Aggregators
}

package "Frontend Layer" {
    component [Bokeh Server] <<frontend>> as Bokeh
    component [Liquidity Distribution Chart] <<frontend>> as PieChart
    component [Token Details Table] <<frontend>> as TokenTable
    component [Dashboard Main] <<frontend>> as DashMain
    component [Kibana Dashboard] <<frontend>> as Kibana
}

package "Web Server Layer" {
    component [Nginx Reverse Proxy] <<proxy>> as Nginx
}

package "Client Layer" {
    component [Web Browser] <<frontend>> as Browser
}

package "Future Components" {
    component [Zilgraph Oracle] <<external>> as Oracle
}

[Zilliqa Blockchain] --> Crawler : Fetch Transaction Data\n(via pyzil)
[Local Zil Seed Node API] --> Crawler : API Calls
CrawlerMgr --> Crawler : Initiates & Manages
ZilswapInt --> [Zilliqa Blockchain] : Query Swap Rates,\nLiquidity, APY

Crawler --> ES : Store Raw\nTransaction Data

DataCollector --> ES : Query & Aggregate\nLiquidity Data
Aggregators --> ES : Query Raw Data
DataCollector --> Mongo : Store Aggregated\nData
Aggregators --> Mongo : Store Processed\nData

Bokeh --> Mongo : Retrieve Aggregated\nData
PieChart --> Bokeh : Renders in
TokenTable --> Bokeh : Renders in
DashMain --> Bokeh : Configures
Kibana --> ES : Query for\nAnalytics Dashboards

Nginx --> Bokeh : Reverse Proxy\n(SSL Termination)
Nginx --> Kibana : Reverse Proxy\n(SSL Termination)

Browser --> Nginx : HTTPS Requests
Nginx --> Browser : HTTPS Responses

Aggregators ..> Oracle : Future: Provide\nAggregated Data
Oracle ..> [Zilliqa Blockchain] : Future: On-Chain\nData Access

note right of Nginx
    SSL/TLS Termination
    HTTP to HTTPS Redirect
    Load Balancing
    Security Enhancement
end note

note right of ES
    Functions as Data Lake
    - Flexible Querying
    - Advanced Aggregations
    - Raw Data Storage
end note

note right of Mongo
    Functions as Data Warehouse
    - Optimized for Dashboard Access
    - Fast Read Performance
    - Aggregated Data Only
end note

note left of Bokeh
    Interactive Visualizations
    - Donut Charts (Liquidity)
    - Tables (Token Details)
    - Custom CSS Styling
end note

@enduml
